vi "newfile.sh"
ctrl q! quits a file without saving
esc ":wq" writes and saves the file
esc gets you out of editing or any other mode
"i" begins text editing in vi
gg gos to the top of the file
G gos to the bottom of the file
:split file1 file2 lets you edit two differnt files at once
:s/hello/hi/g replaces hellow with hi globally
:syntax on typically creates syntax highlighting (colors) helpful for scripting etc
